threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, version 1 (ARM), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a DDoS (Distributed Denial of Service) bot designed for ARM-based IoT devices. It contains a comprehensive suite of attack vectors including UDP, TCP (SYN, ACK, PSH-ACK), ICMP, and SSDP floods. The code explicitly references these attacks in debug strings (e.g., '[udp_plain_flood]', '[syn_flood]', '[icmp_flood]'). It uses raw sockets to manually construct network headers for spoofing and connects to a hardcoded Command and Control (C2) server at IP 5.133.102.226. Additionally, it monitors local network connections by parsing /proc/net/tcp and includes logic for persistent bot operation.
